1. Linux Essentials
• sudo !! - Add sudo to the last command
• ctrl + r - Search history fast
• watch -n 2 cmd - Auto-refresh output
• alias - Quick shortcuts
• man <command> - Quick built-in help

2. Process & System Checks
• ps aux | grep - Find processes
• lsof -i :port - Identify port owner
• df -h - Disk usage
• free -h - Memory snapshot
• htop - Resource overview
• dmesg -T - Kernel events
• kill -9 pid - Kill process

3. Kubernetes Basics
• kubectl get pods -A - Quick overview
• kubectl describe pod - Events/errors
• kubectl logs <pod> - App logs
• kubectl exec -it <pod> - Inspect container
• kubectl top - Resource stats
• kubectl rollout restart - Restart workloads

4. Container Toolkit
• docker ps - Running containers
• docker logs <id> - Debug logs
• docker exec -it <id> - Shell inside
• docker stats - Resource usage
• docker inspect <id> - Detailed metadata
• docker system prune - Cleanup

5. Log Hunters
• grep - Filter text
• awk '{print $1,$9}' access.log - extract pattern & parse field
• sed - Inline edits
• tail -f - Live logs
• less +F - Better tail mode
• journalctl -u <service> - Systemd logs

6. Network Checks
• curl -v - HTTP debugging
• dig + short - DNS lookup
• ss -tunlp - Socket view
• traceroute - Path tracing
• tcpdump -i any - Packet capture

7. File Shortcuts
• find . -name "*.yaml" - Locate files
• rsync -avz - Efficient sync
• tar -xvf - Extract archives
• ln -s - Create symlinks
• chmod +x - Make executable

8. Performance Issues
• top -c - View heavy processes
• iostat -xz 1 - Disk performance
• sar -n DEV 1 - Network stats
• uptime - Load averages
• strace -p <pid> - Syscall tracing
